The paper proposes a method for generating locomotion gaits for snake robots using Model Predictive Control. This involves optimizing trajectories based on the snake dynamics and the environment it is operating in. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the use of optimization techniques and modeling of friction, fluid dynamics, and obstacle avoidance suggest that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-categories.
